# Git Commits

When creating commits for this project:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by:` trailers (including `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or similar).
- Use a concise subject line and optional body — author attribution only via normal git author metadata.
- Do not append bot, agent, or IDE co-author lines unless a human explicitly requests them.

```text
# Good
Fix local dev docs routing and PubMed health probe.

# Bad
Fix local dev docs routing.

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```
